Date:  0/0/1873
Source:  Birds of New Zealand
Author:  BULLER
Vol / Page:  124
Edition:  {1888 2nd edn 1/39-40}
Quote:  MYiOMOiRA TOiTOi. (PiED TiT \{NORTH iSLAND TOMTiT\}.) ... <i>Native names.</i> Miromiro, Komiromiro, \{Pimiromiro,\} Ngirungiru\{, Pingirungiru, and Pipitori\}. ... [40] its note in the early morning is like the Maori syllables <i>ngi-i-ru, ngiru-ngiru</i>, from which it derives its name, the first syllable being rather prolonged.
